  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe assert in
LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF() fires because the VPlan-based cost
model and the legacy cost model disagree on the chosen VF, and the code attempts
to allow such disagreements only when the VPlan contains simplifications not
accounted for by the legacy cost model. In the provided reproducer, a First Order
Recurrence (FOR) phi exists but is unused, so the corresponding
VPInstruction::FirstOrderRecurrenceSplice will be dead and not costed in VPlan.
The legacy model still accounts some cost for such constructs, leading to
disagreement.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug-only run immediately hits the
assertion, with no further logs, indicating the disagreement happens at the first
check in computeBestVF(). The code explicitly guards the assert by calling
planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(...) for both the Best and Legacy plan
widths. If either plan contains unaccounted simplifications, the assert should
not trigger.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nplanContainsAdditionalSimplifications()
is supposed to detect that the VPlan omits certain original loop instructions (a
simplification). It walks the VPlan to collect underlying IR instructions for
recipes and then scans the original loop to find any instructions not covered by
the VPlan or skipped by the cost context. However, it unconditionally ignores all
PHI nodes in the loop header:\n  if (isa<PHINode>(&I) && BB ==
TheLoop->getHeader()) return false;\nThis blanket exclusion prevents detection of
the missing FOR-related PHI when it is dead in the VPlan. As a result,
planContainsAdditionalSimplifications returns false even though the VPlan has
simplified away the FOR splice compared to the legacy model, and the assertion
triggers.\n\nWe should not ignore all header PHIs here. Instead, rely on
CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I, true) to filter out header PHIs that are
irrelevant to cost (e.g., canonical IV), while allowing detection of other PHIs
like FOR-related ones when they are missing from the VPlan.\n\n4. Proposed Edit
Point(s)\n- llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp:7484-7487\n  Change:
Remove the special-case that ignores all header PHI nodes in
planContainsAdditionalSimplifications. This lets the function correctly report
additional simplifications when VPlan drops a header PHI (like FOR) that the
legacy model might still cost. The surrounding logic already calls
CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I, true), so any PHIs that should be ignored for
cost purposes will still be filtered out correctly.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy
deleting the unconditional skip of header PHIs,
planContainsAdditionalSimplifications() will return true when the VPlan contains
additional simplifications such as dropping a dead FOR splice PHI, thereby
allowing the assert to pass in cases where the disagreement is due to legitimate
simplifications. This aligns the verification guard with the intended behavior
and fixes the crash on the provided reproducer without affecting normal cost
computation, since irrelevant PHIs remain filtered by
CostCtx.skipCostComputation.",
